==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gloomy
<hw>Gloom"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Gloomier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Gloomiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Imperfectly
illuminated; dismal through obscurity or darkness; dusky; dim; clouded;
<as>as, the cavern was <ex>gloomy</ex></as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Though hid in
<xex>gloomiest</xex> shade.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Affected with, or expressing, gloom; melancholy;
dejected; <as>as, a <ex>gloomy</ex> temper or
countenance</as>.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Dark; dim; dusky; dismal; cloudy; moody; sullen;
morose; melancholy; sad; downcast; depressed; dejected;
disheartened.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gloppen</ent>⟦br⟧
